Recalls the letters dated 15 December 2015
A/70/623-S/2015/988. and 5 February 2021,
A/75/780-S/2021/179. and recommends that the President of the General Assembly and the President of the Security Council continue the practice of circulating joint letters on the selection and appointment process of the Secretary-General, including outlining notional events, and consider concluding in sufficient time to allow the Secretary-General-designate to prepare for their term in office;
